    {
        "desc": "You stand at the curved corner of an enormous cavern which extends beyond your\nvision to the south and east. Though the floor is perfectly smooth, the walls\nare rough, filled with small niches and knobby rocks jutting into the hall. To\nthe east a great tower rises before you, a mighty peak tipped with snow like\nsilver, but with sheer naked sides, dull red as if stained with blood. With your\nback to the cavern's wall, gazing up at the peak, you can almost believe that\nyou are far away, and that the Dwarves still live in comfort and prosperity.\n",
