        "desc": "There can be no doubt that the dwarven master of this dwelling has begun seeing\nhimself in a rather pompous if not narcissistic fashion; the details of\nfurniture, interior design and decoration are studiously crafted and the focus\nis always the same - Bogger the Dwarf. The walls have been covered with mahogany\npanels, curiously similar to the doors at the throne room of Khazad-dum's high\nlieutenant. Hinged on these panels are drawings showing Bogger during various\nperiods of his life. A collector of rare items and connoisseur of weapons and\narmour, the inhabitant has also filled the room with weapon stands and armour\npegs. A deep, crimson carpet on the floor is kept surprisingly tidy and an\nunmade bed, hinting at the haste at which the dwarf sometimes takes on\nadventures, has been placed in the southeast corner.\n",
